      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "CULDESAC, Idaho. Aug. A.\nThe bodies of c. A. Johnson, Gust\nResell and Andrew Olson, who\nwere killed by a delayed blast on\nthe Northern Pacific extension,\nhave reached the city. They were\nfound 200 feet down the side of the\ncanyon from the point where the\nfatal explosion occurred. Oscar\nOlson, the foreman, received a\nfracture of the skull, a broken leg\nand decorations of the face, but\nis expected to recover. The per-\nsonal effects of the dead men\nwhich have not yet been brought\nin will furnish the only clue to the\nwhereabouts of the relatives."
    }
  ]
